#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:41
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The &kmail; Team welcomes you to &kmail;, a user-friendly email client by "
#| "&kde;. Our goal is to make &kmail; a program that is beautiful and "
#| "intuitive without sacrificing power."
msgid ""
"The &kmail; Team welcomes you to &kmail;, a user-friendly email client by "
"&kde;. Our goal is to make &kmail; a program that is both beautiful and "
"intuitive without sacrificing power."
msgstr ""
"&kmail; 팀은 &kde;의 사용자 친화적 이메일 클라이언트 &kmail; 사용을 환영합니"
"다. 저희의 목표는 &kmail;을 아름답고 직관적으로 가꾸어 나가는 것입니다."

#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have never set up an email client on a &UNIX; system before, we "
"suggest that you read through the <link linkend=\"getting-started\">Getting "
"Started</link> section first."
msgstr ""
"&UNIX; 시스템에서 이메일 클라이언트를 설정해 본 적이 없다면 <link linkend="
"\"getting-started\">시작하기</link> 장을 읽어 보는 것을 추천합니다."

#. Tag: title
#: intro.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some &kmail; Features"
msgstr "&kmail; 주요 기능"

#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:49
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Some links to the great features available in &kmail;"
msgid ""
"Here is a brief guide to some of the great features available in &kmail;"
msgstr "&kmail;의 여러 기능에 대한 링크:"

#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:52
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "You do not have to use your mouse to use &kmail;. Everything can be done "
#| "by using <link linkend=\"keyboard-shortcuts\">Keyboard Shortcuts</link>."
msgid ""
"You do not have to use your mouse when working with &kmail;. Everything can "
"be done with <link linkend=\"keyboard-shortcuts\">Keyboard Shortcuts</link>."
msgstr ""
"&kmail; 사용에는 마우스가 필요하지 않습니다. <link linkend=\"keyboard-"
"shortcuts\">키보드 단축키</link>를 통해서 모든 것을 제어할 수 있습니다."

#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:56
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Although &kmail; can be considered reliable you should keep backups of "
#| "your messages, &ie; use one of the export/archive options listed in <link "
#| "linkend=\"backups\">Backup Options</link> to backup your settings and "
#| "email to a safe place."
msgid ""
"Although &kmail; is very reliable, you should keep backups of your messages, "
"&ie;, use one of the export/archive options listed in <link linkend=\"backups"
"\">Backup Options</link> to back up your settings and email regularly."
msgstr ""
"&kmail;은 안정적이지만 메시지를 주기적으로 백업하는 것을 추천합니다. <link "
"linkend=\"backups\">백업 옵션</link>의 내보내기/보관 옵션을 사용하여 이메일 "
"설정과 메시지 내용을 주기적으로 백업하십시오."

#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:61
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kmail; is capable of importing email in several formats from your "
#| "previous email applications using options in <link linkend=\"import-"
#| "restore\">Restore and Import in &kmail;</link>."
msgid ""
"&kmail; makes it easy to import email from many different email "
"applications. The options are described in <link linkend=\"import-restore"
"\">Restore and Import in &kmail;</link>."
msgstr ""
"&kmail;은 이전에 사용했던 프로그램에서 다양한 형식으로 된 이메일을 가져올 수 "
"있습니다. <link linkend=\"import-restore\">&kmail; 복원 및 가져오기</link>를 "
"참조하십시오."

#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:65
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Organize your folders with ease using &kmail;s extensive <link linkend="
#| "\"folders\">Folders</link> options. Some of the features include handling "
#| "per folder: mailing lists, acl (&imap; only), and archiving."
msgid ""
"You can separate your messages into different categories by using &kmail;'s "
"extensive <link linkend=\"folders\">Folders</link> options. Features include "
"special handling for specified folders: mailing lists, acl (&IMAP; only), "
"and archiving."
msgstr ""
"&kmail;의 <link linkend=\"folders\">폴더</link> 옵션으로 메시지를 폴더 단위"
"로 관리할 수 있습니다. 메일링 리스트, ACL(&imap; 전용) 및 보관 기능은 폴더별"
"로도 사용할 수 있습니다."

#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:69
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Compliment your folder setup with highly configurable <link linkend="
#| "\"filters\">filters</link>."
msgid ""
"You can complement your folder setup with highly configurable <link linkend="
"\"filters\">filters</link>."
msgstr ""
"상세하게 설정할 수 있는 <link linkend=\"filters\">필터</link>로 폴더 설정을 "
"보완하십시오."

#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:72
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "By default &kmail; will detect common email <link linkend=\"configure-"
#| "security-email-scams\">scams</link>. You can also fight SPAM and viruses "
#| "with built in wizards to work with external programs to scan email as it "
#| "comes in. See <link linkend=\"the-anti-spam-wizard\">Anti Spam Wizard</"
#| "link> and <link linkend=\"the-anti-virus-wizard\">Anti-Virus-Wizard</"
#| "link> for details."
msgid ""
"By default &kmail; will detect common email <link linkend=\"configure-"
"security-email-scams\">scams</link>. You can also fight SPAM and viruses by "
"creating filters that work with external programs to scan email as it comes "
"in. See <link linkend=\"the-anti-spam-wizard\">Anti Spam</link> and <link "
"linkend=\"the-anti-virus-wizard\">Anti Virus</link> for details."
msgstr ""
"&kmail;은 기본적으로 잘 알려진 이메일 <link linkend=\"configure-security-"
"email-scams\">사기</link>를 감지할 수 있습니다. 내장 마법사를 통하여 스팸 및 "
"바이러스 이메일을 걸러낼 수 있으며, 외부 필터 프로그램으로 메시지를 검사하도"
"록 설정할 수 있습니다. 자세한 사항은 <link linkend=\"the-anti-spam-wizard\">"
"스팸 방지 마법사</link> 및 <link linkend=\"the-anti-virus-wizard\">바이러스 "
"방지 마법사</link>를 참조하십시오."

#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:78
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Easily manage per-account settings using multiple <link linkend="
#| "\"configure-identity\">identities</link>."
msgid ""
"It's easy to manage several email accounts by using different <link linkend="
"\"configure-identity\">identities</link>."
msgstr ""
"다수의 <link linkend=\"configure-identity\">프로필</link>을 설정하여 계정별 "
"설정을 관리할 수 있습니다."

#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "We hope you will enjoy &kmail;!"
msgstr "&kmail;을 잘 사용하시기를 기대합니다!"

#. Tag: title
#: intro.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid "Getting Help"
msgstr "도움 받기"

#. Tag: para
#: intro.docbook:85
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kmail;'s homepage can be found at <ulink url=\"https://userbase.kde.org/"
#| "Special:MyLanguage/KMail\">https://userbase.kde.org/KMail</ulink>. There "
#| "you will find useful links, &eg; to the user and developer mailing lists. "
#| "Please report bugs in &kmail; using <menuchoice><guimenu>Help</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Report Bug...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgid ""
"&kmail;'s homepage can be found at <ulink url=\"https://apps.kde.org/kmail2/"
"\">https://apps.kde.org/kmail2/</ulink>. There you will find useful links "
"(&eg;, to the user and developer mailing lists, and to the community wiki "
"pages.) Please report any bugs in &kmail; using <menuchoice><guimenu>Help</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Report Bug...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"&kmail; 홈페이지를 방문하려면 <ulink url=\"https://userbase.kde.org/Special:"
"MyLanguage/KMail\">https://userbase.kde.org/KMail</ulink> 사이트로 이동하십시"
"오. 사용자 및 개발자 메일링 리스트 등 도움이 되는 링크를 확인할 수 있습니다. "
"&kmail;의 버그를 보고하려면 <menuchoice><guimenu>도움말</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>버그 보고...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> 항목을 사용하십"
"시오."

